            <p>Johns Hopkins University&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Baltimore&#44; Jan 9 1890<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Dr Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>In answer to your inquiry the<lb/> following&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>Sept. 10 1663 Letters of Denizacon were<lb/> issued to &#34;Jacob alias John Lumbrozo<lb/> ..... late of Lisbone fin the kingdome<lb/> of Portugall having for long time lyved<lb/> within this our Province of Maryland&#34;<lb/></p>
            <p>June 10&#44; 1665 John Lumbrozo petitions<lb/> for and receives a commission to<lb/> trade with the Indians.<lb/></p>
            <p>He was drawn on a jury<lb/></p>
            <p>&#40;These statements are from the<lb/> Archives of Maryland&#41;<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>I enclose you all I know about<lb/> his trial for blasphemy.  I compared<lb/> this with the archives some years<lb/> ago so I can vouch for its correct&#45;<lb/>ness.  Where readings are doubtful<lb/> I have marked &#63;.  I hope this<lb/> answers your purpose.  Will you be<lb/> good enough to return me to the<lb/> enclosed when you have finished with<lb/> it.<lb/>  In haste<lb/> Sincerely Yours<lb/> Cyrus Adler<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
